ed $14.9 billion dollar merger, it\\u2019s the first time that the iconic steelmaker has publicly talked about possible impacts should the merger not be approved by federal regulators.", "score": 0.7672197, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://stainless-steel-world.net/nippon-steel-and-nippon-steel-stainless-steel-corporation-merger", "title": "Nippon Steel and Nippon Steel Stainless Steel Corporation merger - Stainless Steel World", "content": "and Nippon Steel Stainless Steel Corporation (NSSC), a wholly-owned subsidiary of NSC, have announced that their respective Boards of Directors, at meetings held earlier in October, resolved to conduct a merger with NSC as the surviving company and NSSC as the dissolving company, effective as of April 1, 2025.", "score": 0.7402687, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://gmk.center/en/news/biden-plans-to-block-the-merger-of-nippon-steel-and-us-steel-bloomberg", "title": "Biden plans to block the merger of Nippon Steel and US Steel - Bloomberg", "content": "In early December, Nippon Steel reaffirmed its confidence that the acquisition of US Steel could be completed by the end of 2024 if the deal goes through the proper procedures and is approved by the Biden administration.\\n\\nAs GMK Center reported earlier, Japanese Prime Minister Shigeru Ishiba, according to Reuters, sent a letter to the US President asking him to approve the deal so as not to harm recent efforts to strengthen ties between the two countries.\\n\\nTags:", "score": 0.6816637, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://finance.yahoo.com/news/us-steel-nippon-steel-merger-102356390.html", "title": "US Steel and Nippon Steel merger gains non-US regulator approval", "content": "These approvals from the regulatory bodies mark a crucial step towards the completion of the deal, which is anticipated in the second half of 2024.\\n\\nThe bodies approving the transaction include the Directorate-General for Competition of the European Commission, the Mexican Federal Economic Competition Commission, the Serbian Competition Commission, the Ministry of Economy of Slovakia, and the Turkish Competition Authority.", "score": 0.67758125, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.mining-technology.com/news/us-steel-nippon-steel-merger", "title": "US Steel, Nippon Steel merger gains nod of non-US regulators", "content": "United States Steel Corporation (US Steel) and Nippon Steel have secured all regulatory clearances from jurisdictions outside of the US for their proposed merger.\\n\\nThese approvals from the regulatory bodies mark a crucial step towards the completion of the deal, which is anticipated in the second half of 2024.\\n\\n### Go deeper with GlobalData\\n\\nReportsLogo\\n\\n#### Mining Industry Mergers and Acquisitions Deals by Top Themes in Q1 ...\\n\\nReportsLogo", "score": 0.64986813, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://nwindianabusiness.com/community/business-news/u-s-steel-stockholders-approve-merger-with-nippon-steel/64321", "title": "U.S. Steel stockholders approve merger with Nippon Steel \\u2022 Northwest Indiana Business Magazine", "content": "\\u201cThis is an important milestone as we progress toward completing the transaction,\\u201d said David Burritt, U.S. Steel president and CEO, in a press release. \\u201cWe are one step closer to bringing together the best of our companies and moving forward together as the \\u2018Best Steelmaker with World-Leading Capabilities.\\u2019\\u201d\\n\\nBurritt highlighted the merger\'s potential to unite the strengths of both entities, envisioning the emergence of a global powerhouse in steel manufacturing.", "score": 0.5735118, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.foxbusiness.com/politics/trump-biden-oppose-nippon-us-steel-merger-what-vp-harris-position", "title": "Where does VP Harris stand on US Steel-Nippon Steel merger? | Fox Business", "content": "\\"The partnership with Nippon Steel, a long-standing investor in the United States from our close ally Japan, will strengthen the American steel industry, American jobs and American supply chains and enhance the U.S. steel industry\'s competitiveness and resilience against China,\\" U.S. Steel\'s previous statement explained.", "score": 0.55362654, "raw_content": null}, {"url": "https://www.pymnts.com/cpi-posts/us-steel-and-nippon-steel-secure-international-approvals-for-14-9b-merger", "title": "US Steel and Nippon Steel Secure International Approvals for $14.9B Merger", "content": "The U.S. Department of Justice is rigorously examining the proposed transaction. In response to the mounting concerns, Nippon Steel has pledged to honor all existing agreements between U.S. Steel and the union. Additionally, Nippon Steel has committed to relocating its U.S. headquarters to Pittsburgh, where U.S. Steel is currently based, in a bid to alleviate some of the apprehensions surrounding the merger.", "score": 0.53881395, "raw_content": null}]',
